About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

#ccr #creedenceclearwaterrevival #fortunateson

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Apashe & Alina Pash - Kyiv
snippet.description:
This project was filmed in Ukraine during the war. The choir was recorded on a calm day, between nights of air raids and shelling. As I’m writing this, Kyiv is in a blackout.

This city has always meant a great deal to me, and I hope this video can, in one way or another, help people understand what is happening there.

The artist proceeds will be donated to charity. If you'd like to support it further, you'll find a link below.

Charity Link: http://patron8.childrenheroes.org/

Hymns of Resilience EP: https://bit.ly/hymns-of-resilience

snippet.title: KUMA | Bande-annonce 02 ÉP 39 | Sol Yanım (Doublé en Français)
snippet.description:
Kuma | Bande-annonce 02 de l’Épisode 39 (Doublé en Français)
Full Episode → https://youtu.be/Wd6WdNZg04M

Abonnez-vous aujourd’hui et plongez dans l’univers de Kuma ! → 
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCFfH8yBcEGg57loh1b07vGg?sub_confirmation=1

Une voiture fonce sur Karan et il veut des noms, pas du bruit. Ceylan le garde ancré, choisissant le cœur plutôt que le drama. Ailleurs, Leyla cache un “invité” à Ferit pour éviter l’orage, tandis que l’au revoir de la tante et la photo de famille “parfaite” deviennent électriques. Les secrets entrent, l’amour trace ses lignes. Si amour et loyauté s’affrontent ce soir, tu choisis qui ?

À 𝐏𝐑𝐎𝐏𝐎𝐒 𝐃𝐄 𝐊𝐔𝐌𝐀

Amour ou vengeance ? Les deux ont un prix…💔

Ceylan, une mariée en fuite, échappe à sa famille impitoyable et trouve refuge — ainsi qu’une passion électrique — dans les bras de Karan Çelikhan, héritier d’une puissante dynastie. Mais alors que leur romance secrète s’enflamme, un événement tragique fait tout basculer. Coincés entre amour et vengeance, ils doivent affronter des traditions brutales, des secrets familiaux enfouis, et un destin au lourd tribut. 

🔔 Kuma est disponible en exclusivité sur notre chaîne YouTube officielle ➤
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCFfH8yBcEGg57loh1b07vGg?sub_confirmation=1

Portée par Aybüke Yılmaz et Emre Özmen, cette série met en scène un duel bouleversant entre amour, haine et destin. Grâce à son rythme haletant et son intrigue percutante, Kuma captivera les spectateurs semaine après semaine.

≫ Produite par Stellar Yapım, GoQuest Media & VIP 2000
≫ Créatrice de la série : İnci Gülen Oarr
≫ Réalisation : Atilla Cengiz & Irmak Çengel
≫ Directeurs de la photographie : Sinan Onur & Ferhat Özyurt
≫ Musique : Saki Cimen
≫ Scénario : Ahmet Köseoğlu & Gökçen Eroğlu

𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐛𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐩𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐚𝐥𝐞:

Emre Özmen dans le rôle de Karan (rôle principal masculin)
Aybüke Yılmaz dans le rôle de Ceylan (rôle principal féminin)
Hilal Tüfek dans le rôle de Sema (épouse de Salih, belle-sœur de Karan)
Ufuk Kaplan dans le rôle de Kudret Çelikhan (mère de Karan et Salih) 

𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐛𝐮𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐒𝐞𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐝𝐚𝐢𝐫𝐞:

≫ Sezgin Irmak dans le rôle de Salih Çelikhan (frère aîné de Karan)
≫ Ayça Bilir dans le rôle de Aliye Olcay Çelikhan (fille de Salih et Meltem)
≫ Burak Özen dans le rôle de Emir Çelikhan (enfant adoptif d’Hikmet)
≫ Ayşegül Şen dans le rôle de Meltem Olcay (liaison secrète de Salih)

𝙲𝚑𝚊𝚗𝚗𝚎𝚕 𝚖𝚊𝚗𝚊𝚐𝚎𝚍 𝚋𝚢 𝚃𝚞𝚛𝚗𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚁𝚎𝚍 𝙼𝚎𝚍𝚒𝚊𝚌𝚘𝚛𝚙 𝚘𝚗 𝚋𝚎𝚑𝚊𝚕𝚏 𝚘𝚏 𝙶𝚘𝚚𝚞𝚎𝚜𝚝 𝙼𝚎𝚍𝚒𝚊 𝚞𝚗𝚍𝚎𝚛 𝚘𝚞𝚛 “𝚈𝚘𝚞𝚃𝚞𝚋𝚎 𝙵𝚒𝚛𝚜𝚝” 𝚒𝚗𝚒𝚝𝚒𝚊𝚝𝚒𝚟𝚎.

snippet.title: DES FOUS RIRES À LA CHAÎNE, PARDON !! -My Voice Zoo- [DOUBLAGE]
snippet.description:
C'est puéril, mais je recevrai toutes les premières pierres qui me seront lancées avec un sourire suffisant.

My Voice Zoo ! Un petit jeu de simulation de zoo où l'aspect gestion est plus symbolique qu'autre chose, tant les gains d'argent sont plus faits pour vous laisser vous remettre de vos fous rires que pour constituer de la difficulté ! Incarnez une petite choupette nommée Lucy (c'est littéralement tout son lore), dans son travail de doubleuse d'animaux ! Pas besoin de longues études ou de matériel professionnel, juste d'un micro et d'un peu d'inventivité ! Ou d'absurdité immature, c'est selon. C'est ça que de tourner jusqu'à tard dans la nuit aussi, tout est plus drôle quand on manque de sommeil.

Toujours merci à SpongePierre, miniaturiste assermenté et héros de vos coeurs.

Vous pouvez aussi m'suivre sur Twitter/X :
http://x.com/RoiLennon

Bisous et à la prochaine !

snippet.title: Lorna Shore - In Darkness (Official Video)
snippet.description:
Lorna Shore - In Darkness - Official Video. On Tour Now in Europe/UK + North American Tour this spring!

From the new album 'I Feel The Everblack Festering Within Me' - Out Now. Get it now: 
https://ifeeltheeverblackfesteringwithinme.com/
https://lornashoreband.com/

'In Darkness' is about growing up feeling distant from everyone- a song about anxiety and being an outcast (as many of us metal fans grow from). It’s a song about embracing that outlandish and ostracized feeling. Knowing that we have grown in the shadows, the darkness- of the world, but accepting that through that darkness we have become. - WILL RAMOS

LYRICS //

WE ARE ALIVE
I WATCH THE SHADOWS
FALL ON HORIZONS WE ECHO
WE ARE THE DIFFERENCE
A CONGREGATION OF LIKE MINDED HUES AND SEPARATION
AN INTROVERSION OF LIFE
AM I BROKEN, LOST, BATTERED AND TOSSED
I WAS THE ONE ON THE OUTSIDE SEARCHING FOR PEACE I WOULD NEVER FIND
BLACK ROSES LOOM IN THE DARK
NEVER TO FALL APART
WE WERE PERFECTLY SEWN OVER IMPERFECT BONES
WE MADE A HOME IN THE SHADOW OF MADNESS

WE LIVE IN DARKNESS
WE COME TO LIFE
IN DARKNESS WE WON’T DIE
WE WILL SURVIVE
BENEATH THE VALLEYS OF DARKNESS
BETWEEN MOUNTAINS OF DELIVERANCE
WE FOUND A HOME BURIED BELOW
THE SHADOWS IN BETWEEN THE RABBLE WE LET GO
WE’RE NOT MISPLACED, NAUGHT, CURSÈD AND ROT
WE ARE THE ONES BURNING INSIDE
THIS IS HOW IT FEELS TO BE ALIVE
MOONFLOWERS BLOOM IN THE DARK
NEVER TO FALL APART

WE LIVE IN DARKNESS
IN DARKNESS RAVE
EXALT THE FIGHT
IN THIS EMPTINESS WE COME TO LIFE
IN DARKNESS WE ARE ALIVE
WE WERE PERFECTLY SEWN OVER IMPERFECT BONES
WE MADE A HOME IN THE SHADOW OF MADNESS

WE LIVE IN DARKNESS
IN DARKNESS RAVE
EXALT THE FIGHT
IN THIS EMPTINESS WE COME TO LIFE
IN DARKNESS WE ARE ALIVE
WE WILL SURVIVE
IN DARKNESS WE ARE ALIVE

////

snippet.title: End Of Beginning - DJO
snippet.description:

🎤 Lyrics:
Just one more tear to cry, one teardrop from my eye
You better save it for
The middle of the night when things aren't black and white
Enter, Troubadour
"Remember twenty-four?"

[Chorus]
And when I'm back in Chicago, I feel it
Another version of me, I was in it
I wave goodbye to the end of beginning

[Verse 2]
This song has started now, and you're just finding out
Now isn't that a laugh?
A major sacrifice, but clueless at the time
Enter, Caroline
"Just trust me, you'll be fine"
And when I'm back in Chicago, I feel it
Another version of me, I was in it
I wave goodbye to the end of beginning
(Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye, goodbye)

You take the man out of the city, not the city out the man
You take the man out of the city, not the city out the man
You take the man out of the city, not the city out the man
You take the man out of the—

And when I'm back in Chicago, I feel it
Another version of me, I was in it
Oh, I wave goodbye to the end of beginning
(Goodbye, goodbye)

#endofbeginning #djo #asttro
